Executive Summary
This case study documents a comprehensive security assessment conducted on a financial
services payment processing platform. The engagement involved external penetration
testing, infrastructure reconnaissance, and web application security testing across multiple
discovered assets.
The assessment successfully identified critical security vulnerabilities including denial of
service weaknesses, exposed administrative interfaces, and unauthenticated API endpoints.
All findings were documented with detailed remediation guidance, resulting in 100%
resolution of critical issues within two weeks of report delivery.
Key Achievements:
Discovered 600% more attack surface than initially scoped (9 subdomains)
Identified HIGH severity vulnerabilities affecting service availability
Provided actionable remediation roadmap with business impact analysis
Achieved complete remediation verification in follow-up assessment
