SSL/TLS Configuration Analysis
Testing Tool: testssl.sh
Target: Port 443 (HTTPS)
Positive Findings 
Strong Configuration:
TLSv1.3 enabled (most secure)
Modern cipher suites (AES-GCM, ChaCha20-Poly1305)
Not vulnerable to Heartbleed
Strong elliptic curves (Curve25519, Curve448, NIST P-256/384/521)
Perfect Forward Secrecy (PFS) enabled
TLS Fallback SCSV supported
Secure Cryptography:
Preferred Ciphers:- TLS_AES_128_GCM_SHA256- TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384- TLS_CHACHA20_POLY1305_SHA256
Key Exchange:- secp256r1 (NIST P-256)- secp384r1 (NIST P-384)- secp521r1 (NIST P-521)- x25519 (Curve25519)- x448 (Curve448)
Configuration Considerations 
Potential Compatibility Issues:
TLSv1.2 disabled (may affect older clients)
Session renegotiation not supported
Recommendation: Consider enabling TLSv1.2 for backward compatibility while maintaining
TLSv1.3 as preferred.
