Lessons Learned
For Security Assessors
1. Expand reconnaissance beyond initial scope - Subdomain enumeration revealed
800% more attack surface
2. Automated scanning alone is insufficient - Manual validation identified critical issues
3. Prioritize findings by business impact - CVSS alone doesn’t capture real-world risk
4. Clear communication is critical - Executive summaries must balance technical detail
with business context
For Defenders
1. Inventory all external assets - Shadow IT and undocumented infrastructure creates
blind spots
2. Apply security controls consistently - Primary server was secure, but subdomains
were not
3. Administrative interfaces require special protection - Never expose admin panels
publicly
4. Rapid remediation prevents exploitation - Quick response limited exposure window
Recommendations for Similar Organizations
Immediate Actions
1. Asset Discovery:
Conduct comprehensive subdomain enumeration
Document all external-facing services
Map complete attack surface
2. Administrative Access:
Never expose admin interfaces to internet
Implement IP whitelisting
Require MFA for all administrative access
Use VPN for remote admin access
3. API Security:
Implement authentication on all endpoints
Use OAuth 2.0 or JWT tokens
Deploy API gateway
Enable rate limiting
4. Service Hardening:
